              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/essay/ways-we-survive-or-how-fiction-helps-us-understand-violence-catalina-infante-beovic" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Infante-anchor.jpg?itok=GMujACTn" width="250" height="175" alt="A collage of the three covers to the books discussed below" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/essay/ways-we-survive-or-how-fiction-helps-us-understand-violence-catalina-infante-beovic">Ways We Survive (or How Fiction Helps Us to Understand Violence)</a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/catalina-infante-beovic" hreflang="en">Catalina Infante Beovic</a>
</span></div>
        </li>
              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/essay/simorgh-exile-reimagining-iranian-diaspora-fereshteh-molavis-thirty-shadow-birds" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Ezzati-anchor.jpg?itok=K_OrFK5a" width="250" height="175" alt="Fereshteh Molavi with the cover to her book Thirty Shadow Birds" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/essay/simorgh-exile-reimagining-iranian-diaspora-fereshteh-molavis-thirty-shadow-birds">Simorgh in Exile: Reimagining Iranian Diaspora in Fereshteh Molavi’s <em>…</a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/mahdiyeh-ezzati" hreflang="en">Mahdiyeh Ezzati</a>
</span></div>
        </li>
              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/essay/phonetic-uterus-journey-through-language-and-identity-arya-gopi" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Gopi-anchor.jpg?itok=LiXtwZkr" width="250" height="175" alt="An illustration of a human figure lying on its back in a river with a boat floating nearby and large plants rising from the water" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

