</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-thumbnail"><div class="field-content imageleft">  <a href="/blog/essay/simorgh-exile-reimagining-iranian-diaspora-fereshteh-molavis-thirty-shadow-birds" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/blog_thumbnail/public/Ezzati-anchor.jpg?itok=VXJKyXsx" width="100" height="75" alt="Fereshteh Molavi with the cover to her book Thirty Shadow Birds" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-blog-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><h4 class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/essay/simorgh-exile-reimagining-iranian-diaspora-fereshteh-molavis-thirty-shadow-birds">Simorgh in Exile: Reimagining Iranian Diaspora in Fereshteh Molavi’s <em>Thirty Shadow Birds</em></a>
</h4></div><div><div class="blog-summary">

Photo of Fereshteh Molavi by Pari Riahi

